name: THON
description: THON is a student-run philanthropy committed to enhancing the lives of children and families impacted by childhood cancer. Our mission is to provide emotional and financial support, spread awareness, and ensure funding for critical research — all in pursuit of a cure.

name: MIMA Music
description: Modern Improvisational Music Appreciation (MIMA) is a 501(c)(3) music education nonprofit that engages and enriches communities through music improvisation and collaborative songwriting.

name: Special Operations Fund
description: To provide educational grants and support to the families of special mission unit warriors killed in action, killed in training or who died in the line of duty. We also support the families of current and veteran special mission units' warriors with merit scholarships and other educational opportunities.

name: ALS Cure Project
description: The purpose of the ALS Cure Project is to provide laser focused leadership and sponsor scientific research leading to a cure for ALS (also known as Lou Gehrig’s Disease) through collaborations with research organizations and biotech and pharma companies.

name: Camp CARE
description: Camp CARE is committed to providing a camp and other year-round activities for children up to age 16, who have or had cancer, and their families in the Charlotte, NC area.

name: In A Heartbeat
description: Our mission is to prevent death from hypertrophic cardiomyopathy (HCM) and sudden cardiac arrest by raising awareness, enabling research, and donating automated external defibrillators (AEDs) to places that need them.

name: Experience Camps
description: We give grieving children experiences that will change their lives forever. Experience camps is a national, no-cost program for grieving children who have experienced the death of a parent, sibling or primary caregiver. Our one-week, overnight summer camp and year-round programs help to reframe the experience of grief and empower kids to develop invaluable coping skills that enable them to move forward with their lives. Through compassion, connection, and play, experience camps empowers grieving children to embody a life full of hope and possibility.

name: Capital Area Food Bank
description: Together with 450 nonprofit organizations in Washington DC, we provide 30 million meals to almost half a million area residents, every year. And because we know that food alone won’t solve hunger, we also address the root causes of hunger through multiple education programs and innovative service delivery partnerships.

name: United Spinal Association
description: United Spinal's mission is to enhance the quality of the lives of people living with spinal cord injury or disease, as well as disabled veterans, through the provision of resources, information and representation.
